Emit TCPM (USB Power Delivery) state machine transitions to the kernel ring
buffer so they appear on the serial console during boot.

Without this patch, all TCPM debug output goes only into a debugfs circular
buffer (/sys/kernel/debug/tcpm/*/log), which is inaccessible without an
interactive shell. On the Cubie A7S the display isn't working yet (DP Alt Mode
negotiation is the active debugging target), so there is no display and no
getty on the serial port — the boot log IS the only diagnostic channel.

Adding dev_info() after the vsnprintf makes every PD state transition (CC
detection, Source_Capabilities, VDM Discover_Identity/SVIDs/Modes, Enter_Mode,
orientation/mode switch) visible in the serial output at loglevel >= 6.

This is a temporary debug patch. Remove once DP Alt Mode is confirmed working.

--- a/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
@@ -619,6 +619,8 @@

 	vsnprintf(tmpbuffer, sizeof(tmpbuffer), fmt, args);

+	dev_info(port->dev, "TCPM: %s\n", tmpbuffer);
+
 	if (tcpm_log_full(port)) {
 		port->logbuffer_head = max(port->logbuffer_head - 1, 0);
 		strcpy(tmpbuffer, "overflow");
